1
00:00:08,733 --> 00:00:11,767
<i>They betrayed me
inside our own home!</i>

2
00:00:11,900 --> 00:00:13,167
<i> I am the victim here.</i>

3
00:00:13,300 --> 00:00:14,933
She abused my kindness.

4
00:00:15,067 --> 00:00:16,167
<i> You, animal!</i>

5
00:00:16,300 --> 00:00:19,800
<i>You are your dad's favorite,
but for heaven's sake,</i>

6
00:00:19,933 --> 00:00:22,700
<i>do not be as evil
as your father.</i>

7
00:00:22,833 --> 00:00:24,033
<i> Why did you keep it from me?</i>

8
00:00:24,167 --> 00:00:26,933
<i>For what? To cover up
what your mother was doing?</i>

9
00:00:27,067 --> 00:00:29,967
<i>You are the pests destroying
this house!</i>

10
00:00:30,100 --> 00:00:33,433
<i>You are a curse
to the Torrecampo family!</i>

11
00:01:21,067 --> 00:01:22,167
Yolly,

12
00:01:22,300 --> 00:01:24,400
have you seen Mama Regina?

13
00:01:24,533 --> 00:01:26,500
[TENSE]

14
00:01:31,233 --> 00:01:32,233
Why, Ma'am?

15
00:01:32,367 --> 00:01:34,933
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

16
00:01:39,700 --> 00:01:40,567
Co-in-law.

17
00:01:40,700 --> 00:01:42,800
[SLAPS]

18
00:01:42,967 --> 00:01:44,533
Don't call me co-in-law!

19
00:01:44,667 --> 00:01:47,333
That title is for extended
family only

20
00:01:47,467 --> 00:01:49,000
not for freeloading predators

21
00:01:49,133 --> 00:01:51,467
who can't keep
their legs closed!

22
00:01:51,600 --> 00:01:52,700
What?

23
00:01:52,833 --> 00:01:56,200
You must have been thrilled
when you fooled me, right?

24
00:01:56,333 --> 00:01:58,200
What? Were you smiling
every time

25
00:01:58,333 --> 00:02:01,567
you unbuckled my husband's belt?

26
00:02:01,700 --> 00:02:03,567
Were you laughing at me
every time

27
00:02:03,700 --> 00:02:05,867
you kissed his filthy mouth?

28
00:02:07,167 --> 00:02:09,633
I thought you only wanted
secondhand bags,

29
00:02:09,767 --> 00:02:11,500
but it turns out you wanted
secondhand affection

30
00:02:11,633 --> 00:02:12,967
from my husband!

31
00:02:13,100 --> 00:02:16,067
I thought you were here
for your daughter, but no!

32
00:02:16,233 --> 00:02:19,533
You were actually here providing
extra service for the landlord!

33
00:02:19,667 --> 00:02:21,267
You make me sick!

34
00:02:23,133 --> 00:02:26,600
Mom, my mother was just tempted.

35
00:02:26,733 --> 00:02:29,267
She made a mistake but she
is not a bad person.

36
00:02:29,400 --> 00:02:30,900
A mistake, Marj?

37
00:02:31,033 --> 00:02:33,500
You make a mistake when you
overcook pasta

38
00:02:33,633 --> 00:02:35,667
or wear off-season couture,

39
00:02:35,800 --> 00:02:39,200
but what your mother did
was ambush my marriage!

40
00:02:39,333 --> 00:02:41,567
I thought you were my friend!

41
00:02:41,700 --> 00:02:44,000
I trusted you!

42
00:02:44,133 --> 00:02:46,767
But you were just
a professional scavenger

43
00:02:46,900 --> 00:02:49,233
waiting for my leftovers!

44
00:02:49,400 --> 00:02:51,067
[SOBBING]

45
00:02:53,467 --> 00:02:56,967
Regina, forgive me.

46
00:02:57,100 --> 00:03:00,033
I regret what I did.

47
00:03:00,167 --> 00:03:01,267
I was just tempted.

48
00:03:01,400 --> 00:03:04,667
I was tempted
by my loneliness, Regina.

49
00:03:04,800 --> 00:03:07,467
I don't care how lonely
you were!

50
00:03:07,600 --> 00:03:08,833
How lonely you were!

51
00:03:08,967 --> 00:03:12,167
Loneliness is not an excuse
for you to cheat!

52
00:03:12,300 --> 00:03:13,700
Do you know what you are?

53
00:03:13,833 --> 00:03:15,233
You're a knockoff bag!

54
00:03:15,367 --> 00:03:16,933
From a distance you look fine,

55
00:03:17,067 --> 00:03:22,633
but up close it's obvious
how fake you are!

56
00:03:22,800 --> 00:03:24,500
- [SLAPS]
- [GRUMBLES]

57
00:03:26,633 --> 00:03:28,467
What? Go ahead,

58
00:03:28,600 --> 00:03:30,167
defend your mother!

59
00:03:30,300 --> 00:03:33,767
It just proves how undignified
you are, just like your mother!

60
00:03:33,900 --> 00:03:35,500
[INTENSE]

61
00:03:35,633 --> 00:03:37,467
[CLAMORING]

62
00:03:37,600 --> 00:03:42,100
Hurt me instead, but don't hurt
my child!

63
00:03:42,233 --> 00:03:43,700
- Mom!
- [INTENSE]

64
00:03:45,500 --> 00:03:47,267
- Stop it!
- [SOBBING]

65
00:03:47,400 --> 00:03:48,900
Marj.

66
00:03:49,033 --> 00:03:50,833
Mom.

67
00:03:50,967 --> 00:03:53,000
- Don't hurt my mother!
- [CLAMORING]

68
00:03:53,133 --> 00:03:54,067
Wait.

69
00:03:54,233 --> 00:03:56,400
Let me go.

70
00:03:56,533 --> 00:03:58,067
What is happening?

71
00:03:58,200 --> 00:04:00,667
This two-faced woman
and your father,

72
00:04:01,700 --> 00:04:07,200
they have been turning our house
into a cheap roadside motel!

73
00:04:07,333 --> 00:04:11,467
They betrayed me inside
our own home!

74
00:04:11,600 --> 00:04:12,700
No, Mom.

75
00:04:12,833 --> 00:04:14,900
- You must be mistaken.
- I'm not mistaken!

76
00:04:15,033 --> 00:04:16,167
Dad,

77
00:04:16,300 --> 00:04:17,767
is this true?

78
00:04:17,900 --> 00:04:19,967
- [SOBBING]
- [INTENSE]

79
00:04:26,867 --> 00:04:28,933
She was the one flirting
with me.

80
00:04:32,667 --> 00:04:36,500
I rejected her advances
many times.

81
00:04:37,533 --> 00:04:41,367
But I felt sorry

82
00:04:41,500 --> 00:04:43,300
because

83
00:04:43,433 --> 00:04:45,033
she looked desperate.

84
00:04:47,367 --> 00:04:50,733
If anything,

85
00:04:50,867 --> 00:04:53,700
I am the victim here.

86
00:04:53,833 --> 00:04:55,600
She abused my kindness.

87
00:04:55,733 --> 00:04:57,433
- Mom, Mom, Mom!
- Mom!

88
00:04:57,567 --> 00:04:59,600
- Your a liar.
- Mom!

89
00:04:59,733 --> 00:05:02,033
You were the one who seduced me!

90
00:05:02,200 --> 00:05:03,267
You!

91
00:05:03,400 --> 00:05:05,033
What happened between us?

92
00:05:05,167 --> 00:05:07,700
It happened only once.

93
00:05:07,833 --> 00:05:10,867
Because you took advantage
of my loneliness!

94
00:05:11,000 --> 00:05:12,667
- Mom.
- You, animal!

95
00:05:12,800 --> 00:05:14,533
- Mom.
- You, animal!

96
00:05:15,833 --> 00:05:17,433
I don't understand.

97
00:05:17,567 --> 00:05:19,267
Why are they fighting?

98
00:05:19,400 --> 00:05:20,767
Weren't Grandmother
and Grandmother Evelyn

99
00:05:20,900 --> 00:05:22,133
already getting along?

100
00:05:23,500 --> 00:05:25,967
I think it's because
of grandfather, cousin.

101
00:05:26,100 --> 00:05:27,900
Should we go down there
and stop them?

102
00:05:28,033 --> 00:05:29,233
But no!

103
00:05:29,367 --> 00:05:32,133
You can't get stressed, right?

104
00:05:32,267 --> 00:05:34,200
You know what, I'll be the one
to go down.

105
00:05:35,267 --> 00:05:37,567
[CLAMORING IN DISTANCE]

106
00:05:41,467 --> 00:05:43,367
They're fighting!

107
00:05:43,500 --> 00:05:44,867
- Noisy!
- Uncle Jobert!

108
00:05:45,000 --> 00:05:46,500
Noisy! Noisy!

109
00:05:46,633 --> 00:05:47,967
- Noisy!
- Uncle Jobert!

110
00:05:48,100 --> 00:05:49,033
Noisy!

111
00:05:49,167 --> 00:05:50,600
- Noisy! Noisy!
- Uncle Jobert doesn't like

112
00:05:50,733 --> 00:05:51,767
- people shouting, right?
- Noisy!

113
00:05:51,900 --> 00:05:53,233
Noisy!

114
00:05:53,367 --> 00:05:55,433
- Ah, the headphones.
- Noisy!

115
00:05:55,567 --> 00:05:56,333
- Noisy!
- Hurry.

116
00:05:56,467 --> 00:05:57,900
- Uncle Jobert, here it is.
- Noisy!

117
00:05:58,033 --> 00:05:59,100
Noisy.

118
00:05:59,233 --> 00:06:01,267
[INTENSE]

119
00:06:15,200 --> 00:06:17,000
My mother really planned
approaching you

120
00:06:17,133 --> 00:06:19,533
to confess what happened.

121
00:06:20,967 --> 00:06:23,200
She truly regrets it.

122
00:06:23,333 --> 00:06:25,833
She values your friendship.

123
00:06:25,967 --> 00:06:30,033
- She didn't intend...
- That's not regret.

124
00:06:30,167 --> 00:06:31,833
That's called...

125
00:06:31,967 --> 00:06:33,633
panic mode.

126
00:06:33,767 --> 00:06:35,667
Damage control.

127
00:06:35,800 --> 00:06:37,567
She wants to clear herself

128
00:06:37,700 --> 00:06:41,100
so she won't lose her free pass
in this household.

129
00:06:44,333 --> 00:06:46,033
And don't pretend

130
00:06:46,167 --> 00:06:48,900
that you value our friendship.

131
00:06:49,033 --> 00:06:51,233
Because when you saw a crack
in my marriage,

132
00:06:51,367 --> 00:06:54,000
you pushed in like a termite.

133
00:06:54,133 --> 00:06:57,100
You did that just to stab me
in the back, Evelyn.

134
00:06:57,233 --> 00:07:00,200
You did it while eating
from my fine bone china!

135
00:07:00,333 --> 00:07:01,433
- [CLAMORING]
- Mom! Mom!

136
00:07:01,567 --> 00:07:03,267
- Let go of me!
- Stop.

137
00:07:03,400 --> 00:07:05,233
- Mom!
- Let go of me!

138
00:07:05,367 --> 00:07:08,500
- Let go of me, Edward.
- [SOBBING]

139
00:07:08,633 --> 00:07:10,233
Come on, come on, okay.

140
00:07:10,367 --> 00:07:12,600
Let's go.

141
00:07:12,733 --> 00:07:14,167
Where are you going?

142
00:07:16,067 --> 00:07:17,267
You've been exposed already!

143
00:07:17,400 --> 00:07:19,133
- Don't get involved anymore!
- [SOBBING]

144
00:07:19,267 --> 00:07:21,267
[INTENSE]

145
00:07:23,200 --> 00:07:24,367
[SOBBING]

146
00:07:24,500 --> 00:07:26,100
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

147
00:07:40,233 --> 00:07:41,167
You know what?

148
00:07:41,300 --> 00:07:43,533
Ma'am Regina's anger is really
different today.

149
00:07:43,667 --> 00:07:46,333
It feels like the fire
is stronger.

150
00:07:47,833 --> 00:07:50,467
Yolly, I wish you hadn't told
on them.

151
00:07:50,600 --> 00:07:52,733
There wouldn't have been
any trouble.

152
00:07:52,867 --> 00:07:54,200
That's why I exposed this,

153
00:07:54,333 --> 00:07:57,467
my loyalty was
with Ma'am Regina.

154
00:07:57,600 --> 00:08:00,767
And what do you gain
from being loyal to her?

155
00:08:01,833 --> 00:08:05,500
Aren't you afraid to side
with her in front of Sir Greg?

156
00:08:05,633 --> 00:08:08,667
Sir Greg is the king
of this palace.

157
00:08:10,067 --> 00:08:11,233
Oscar,

158
00:08:11,367 --> 00:08:16,867
I had to do what I did
as a woman.

159
00:08:17,000 --> 00:08:18,600
You?

160
00:08:18,733 --> 00:08:21,367
What if I go completely blind?

161
00:08:21,533 --> 00:08:23,733
I know she won't abandon me.

162
00:08:23,867 --> 00:08:26,667
She will never abandon my
family.

163
00:08:30,400 --> 00:08:33,267
There.

164
00:08:33,400 --> 00:08:35,533
So there really
was a hidden agenda.

165
00:08:41,467 --> 00:08:44,067
So that's what you were talking
about last night.

166
00:08:44,200 --> 00:08:45,067
<i> I asked you, remember?</i>

167
00:08:45,200 --> 00:08:46,500
<i> I even pushed you about it!</i>

168
00:08:46,633 --> 00:08:48,933
Why did you keep it from me?

169
00:08:49,067 --> 00:08:50,533
For what?

170
00:08:50,667 --> 00:08:54,067
To cover up what your mother
was doing?

171
00:08:54,200 --> 00:08:57,600
As far as I know, both she
and your father were at fault.

172
00:08:57,767 --> 00:08:59,333
That's not the point!

173
00:08:59,467 --> 00:09:02,933
By doing that, you didn't think
about how my mother would feel.

174
00:09:03,067 --> 00:09:05,633
Because I was thinking
about how you would feel!

175
00:09:05,767 --> 00:09:08,133
I was afraid you would get angry
at my mother

176
00:09:08,267 --> 00:09:10,467
and that it would affect
our relationship.

177
00:09:10,600 --> 00:09:13,000
Because I hid it from you,
and now that you know,

178
00:09:13,133 --> 00:09:15,067
I was right about my fear.

179
00:09:15,200 --> 00:09:17,767
Do you think I wouldn't
understand you?

180
00:09:17,900 --> 00:09:19,767
I know Dad.

181
00:09:19,900 --> 00:09:22,967
I know it wasn't your mother
who approached him first.

182
00:09:23,100 --> 00:09:25,000
I could have done something
about it

183
00:09:25,133 --> 00:09:27,733
before Mom found out.

184
00:09:27,900 --> 00:09:30,200
If only you told me.

185
00:09:30,333 --> 00:09:34,233
I'm angry at you not because
your mother got involved.

186
00:09:34,367 --> 00:09:37,200
I'm angry because you
didn't tell me the truth.

187
00:09:37,333 --> 00:09:39,267
It made it seem

188
00:09:39,400 --> 00:09:41,133
like you were tolerating them!

189
00:09:42,767 --> 00:09:45,800
I'm sorry, I wasn't thinking.

190
00:09:45,933 --> 00:09:49,567
You're damn right,
you weren't thinking!

191
00:09:49,700 --> 00:09:52,433
And now my family
is falling apart!

192
00:09:52,567 --> 00:09:56,100
[DRAMATIC]

193
00:10:12,133 --> 00:10:13,133
Hey! Hey! Hey!

194
00:10:13,267 --> 00:10:14,367
- Hey, Ash.
- [CHUCKLES]

195
00:10:14,500 --> 00:10:16,667
- What's up with you?
- I didn't know you were biking

196
00:10:16,800 --> 00:10:18,867
- around the village.
- Just now.

197
00:10:19,000 --> 00:10:20,900
- I'm already tired.
- [CHUCKLES]

198
00:10:21,200 --> 00:10:23,600
And it's BV at home right now.

199
00:10:23,733 --> 00:10:25,167
- Bad vibes?
- Yes.

200
00:10:25,300 --> 00:10:26,167
Is it Jas?

201
00:10:26,300 --> 00:10:27,533
Is everything okay?

202
00:10:27,667 --> 00:10:29,633
No, it's not, couz.

203
00:10:29,767 --> 00:10:33,600
There's major friction among the
grown-ups at home right now.

204
00:10:33,733 --> 00:10:35,500
Well, I know it might cheer
you up.

205
00:10:35,667 --> 00:10:37,767
There's a new bike
and skate park around here.

206
00:10:37,900 --> 00:10:40,433
Maybe we can go there tomorrow?

207
00:10:42,667 --> 00:10:44,833
But Jas isn't allowed.

208
00:10:44,967 --> 00:10:46,167
That's too bad.

209
00:10:46,300 --> 00:10:48,533
I wanted to bring her there too.

210
00:10:48,667 --> 00:10:51,667
Maybe next time when she's
feeling better.

211
00:10:51,800 --> 00:10:52,800
But for now,

212
00:10:52,933 --> 00:10:54,567
can it just be the two of us?

213
00:10:54,700 --> 00:10:55,867
So, go?

214
00:10:56,000 --> 00:10:58,300
Go! Let's go!

215
00:10:58,433 --> 00:10:59,833
Are you going to the clubhouse?

216
00:10:59,967 --> 00:11:01,733
Yeah, I'm just gonna grab
some drinks.

217
00:11:01,867 --> 00:11:02,867
- Come on, let's go together.
- Sure.

218
00:11:03,000 --> 00:11:04,100
Okay, let's go.

219
00:11:07,100 --> 00:11:09,967
Finish it, dear,
so it won't go to waste.

220
00:11:10,133 --> 00:11:12,900
Yes, Mom.

221
00:11:13,033 --> 00:11:14,433
Thank you.

222
00:11:17,700 --> 00:11:18,900
Eat now, dear.

223
00:11:20,800 --> 00:11:29,133
[SPEAKS IN VISAYAN LANGUAGE]

224
00:11:29,267 --> 00:11:31,033
I understand, Marj.

225
00:11:32,967 --> 00:11:35,267
We can't go back
to the old apartment anymore

226
00:11:35,400 --> 00:11:37,300
because Hannah already left.

227
00:11:37,433 --> 00:11:39,567
We need to find a new one.

228
00:11:45,233 --> 00:11:46,400
Marj.

229
00:11:48,833 --> 00:11:50,800
You're right.

230
00:11:52,767 --> 00:11:55,700
Even your relationship
with Paolo

231
00:11:55,833 --> 00:11:58,300
was affected

232
00:11:58,433 --> 00:12:00,600
because of the mistake I made.

233
00:12:02,933 --> 00:12:04,033
It's okay, Mom.

234
00:12:05,700 --> 00:12:09,567
My whole life, I've always been
the one cleaning up your messes.

235
00:12:12,300 --> 00:12:13,900
It's just tiring.

236
00:12:15,433 --> 00:12:17,200
So, I hope this
is the last time.

237
00:12:20,233 --> 00:12:21,433
Mom,

238
00:12:22,467 --> 00:12:25,600
everything will be okay.

239
00:12:25,733 --> 00:12:30,333
Just say sorry to sister so she
won't be angry anymore.

240
00:12:30,467 --> 00:12:32,367
[DRAMATIC]

241
00:12:37,833 --> 00:12:38,800
Sorry.

242
00:12:38,933 --> 00:12:40,800
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

243
00:12:56,733 --> 00:12:57,633
[KNOCKS]

244
00:12:57,767 --> 00:12:59,900
I already said I don't want
to eat!

245
00:13:04,267 --> 00:13:05,967
Mom, it's me.

246
00:13:13,433 --> 00:13:15,467
They said you haven't eaten yet.

247
00:13:17,633 --> 00:13:19,033
Have some soup at least.

248
00:13:19,167 --> 00:13:20,900
[PENSIVE]

249
00:13:27,033 --> 00:13:28,733
Mom,

250
00:13:28,867 --> 00:13:31,500
I'm getting worried
about you.

251
00:13:31,633 --> 00:13:34,033
You might end up getting sick.

252
00:13:35,300 --> 00:13:37,567
Nothing hurts more than

253
00:13:37,700 --> 00:13:40,833
the betrayal done to me
by your father

254
00:13:40,967 --> 00:13:42,833
and Marj's mother.

255
00:13:45,133 --> 00:13:46,033
I know.

256
00:13:47,767 --> 00:13:49,667
And I'm sorry for what she did.

257
00:13:51,133 --> 00:13:52,100
But Dad?

258
00:13:53,133 --> 00:13:54,600
We both know

259
00:13:54,767 --> 00:13:56,900
this isn't the first time
he cheated.

260
00:13:59,033 --> 00:14:00,467
[DRAMATIC]

261
00:14:03,100 --> 00:14:05,100
I know.

262
00:14:05,233 --> 00:14:10,067
But I never thought he would do
it inside our own house.

263
00:14:10,200 --> 00:14:11,733
Who's next? The maids?

264
00:14:22,600 --> 00:14:24,033
It's just sad

265
00:14:25,633 --> 00:14:30,633
because I was starting to treat
Evelyn as a friend.

266
00:14:30,800 --> 00:14:32,467
And you know,

267
00:14:34,133 --> 00:14:36,500
I don't trust that easily.

268
00:14:36,633 --> 00:14:37,500
You know that.

269
00:14:37,633 --> 00:14:38,867
[DRAMATIC]

270
00:14:41,367 --> 00:14:43,800
She knew about my problems
with Greg.

271
00:14:46,900 --> 00:14:48,167
She...

272
00:14:48,300 --> 00:14:50,300
she knew about my life.

273
00:14:53,833 --> 00:14:55,033
She knew

274
00:14:56,333 --> 00:15:00,267
how deep my pain was toward
your father.

275
00:15:04,400 --> 00:15:05,667
Your dad...

276
00:15:07,567 --> 00:15:11,400
he is my world.

277
00:15:11,533 --> 00:15:14,967
I never loved anyone but him.

278
00:15:17,133 --> 00:15:19,633
- I know.
- [MUSIC CONTINUES]

279
00:15:24,833 --> 00:15:28,800
I wish he had just told me what
was lacking.

280
00:15:30,533 --> 00:15:33,533
What was wrong so I could
have changed it.

281
00:15:36,833 --> 00:15:39,300
Instead of deceiving me.

282
00:15:43,033 --> 00:15:46,600
Maybe then I could have been
worthy to him again

283
00:15:49,233 --> 00:15:52,967
so he wouldn't look for what was
missing in me somewhere else.

284
00:15:53,100 --> 00:15:56,233
[DRAMATIC]

285
00:15:59,567 --> 00:16:01,300
I never had any proof

286
00:16:01,433 --> 00:16:04,667
that your dad was cheating
on me, Paolo.

287
00:16:07,933 --> 00:16:09,567
But now I do.

288
00:16:11,600 --> 00:16:13,933
And he even admitted
it to me himself.

289
00:16:16,500 --> 00:16:18,400
That's why the pain
hurts even more.

290
00:16:18,533 --> 00:16:19,967
[DRAMATIC]

291
00:16:22,433 --> 00:16:26,400
Your father didn't just lie
to me.

292
00:16:26,533 --> 00:16:30,100
He disrespected me inside
my own house!

293
00:16:32,900 --> 00:16:36,967
It's like I never mattered.

294
00:16:37,100 --> 00:16:40,567
It's like my existence
lost its meaning.

295
00:16:42,267 --> 00:16:46,167
It's as if he killed me.

296
00:16:46,300 --> 00:16:47,333
I wish...

297
00:16:48,967 --> 00:16:52,167
I wish he had just killed me!

298
00:16:52,300 --> 00:16:54,233
[DRAMATIC]

299
00:16:57,700 --> 00:16:59,500
[SOBBING]

300
00:17:08,200 --> 00:17:10,067
I feel sorry for Grandmother

301
00:17:10,200 --> 00:17:13,500
She must feel really devastated.

302
00:17:13,633 --> 00:17:15,900
Weng also told me about it.

303
00:17:16,067 --> 00:17:19,333
She hasn't come out of her room
since last night.

304
00:17:21,867 --> 00:17:23,333
This wouldn't have happened

305
00:17:23,467 --> 00:17:25,600
if Grandfather and Grandmother
Evelyn had controlled

306
00:17:25,733 --> 00:17:27,200
their feelings.

307
00:17:27,333 --> 00:17:28,367
I mean,

308
00:17:28,500 --> 00:17:29,900
it's weird.

309
00:17:30,033 --> 00:17:33,667
We're like one whole family yet
they still did that.

310
00:17:33,800 --> 00:17:34,867
You know, couz,

311
00:17:35,000 --> 00:17:37,800
sometimes when a person
is really lonely,

312
00:17:37,933 --> 00:17:41,367
they really lose
their common sense.

313
00:17:41,500 --> 00:17:44,300
Maybe that's what really
happened to your grandmother

314
00:17:44,433 --> 00:17:46,033
and grandfather, right?

315
00:17:48,833 --> 00:17:51,233
I love my Grandmother Evelyn.

316
00:17:51,367 --> 00:17:54,167
And I don't want to judge her.

317
00:17:54,300 --> 00:17:55,600
But I wish she
had thought that

318
00:17:55,733 --> 00:17:58,700
it might break people's
trust in her.

319
00:18:00,100 --> 00:18:02,200
She shouldn't have
betrayed anyone.

320
00:18:02,333 --> 00:18:04,033
Especially family.

321
00:18:05,633 --> 00:18:06,667
And now look.

322
00:18:06,800 --> 00:18:09,800
Her friendship
with grandmother Regina

323
00:18:09,933 --> 00:18:13,767
and her relationship
with the entire family.

324
00:18:13,900 --> 00:18:15,367
But, couz,

325
00:18:15,500 --> 00:18:19,233
what if they didn't mean
for it to happen, right?

326
00:18:19,367 --> 00:18:22,333
What if things
just really happened?

327
00:18:22,500 --> 00:18:23,733
Like...

328
00:18:23,867 --> 00:18:26,233
You know,
there are feelings that

329
00:18:26,367 --> 00:18:28,400
even if you don't invite them,

330
00:18:28,533 --> 00:18:31,033
they suddenly arrive.

331
00:18:31,167 --> 00:18:33,233
Maybe she was just weak.

332
00:18:33,367 --> 00:18:35,800
But does that really
make her a villain?

333
00:18:36,867 --> 00:18:39,033
Don't justify it, Ash.

334
00:18:39,167 --> 00:18:40,933
That's still betrayal.

335
00:18:41,067 --> 00:18:44,867
Being weak is not an
excuse to ruin lives.

336
00:18:45,000 --> 00:18:47,067
Especially family.

337
00:18:47,200 --> 00:18:50,133
You just don't go after
anyone you know is off limits.

338
00:18:50,267 --> 00:18:51,467
Period.

339
00:18:55,500 --> 00:18:58,200
Jas, take your meds first.

340
00:18:58,333 --> 00:19:00,000
Wait a bit, couz.

341
00:19:00,133 --> 00:19:02,000
Okay.

342
00:19:02,133 --> 00:19:04,433
[UNSETTLING]

343
00:19:14,033 --> 00:19:16,167
[PHONE KEYS CLICKING]

344
00:19:17,633 --> 00:19:18,567
Sorry,

345
00:19:18,700 --> 00:19:20,933
I can't come with you tomorrow.

346
00:19:21,067 --> 00:19:23,433
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

347
00:19:32,700 --> 00:19:36,567
[DRAMATIC]

348
00:19:45,000 --> 00:19:46,200
Paolo.

349
00:19:48,500 --> 00:19:50,133
I know,

350
00:19:50,267 --> 00:19:52,633
you are your dad's favorite.

351
00:19:54,400 --> 00:19:55,767
And I know

352
00:19:56,933 --> 00:19:59,433
you're following his footsteps.

353
00:20:00,933 --> 00:20:03,033
But please,

354
00:20:04,100 --> 00:20:06,233
don't be like him.

355
00:20:06,367 --> 00:20:11,200
Please, Paolo, listen to me!

356
00:20:11,333 --> 00:20:16,267
Do not be as evil
as your father, please!

357
00:20:16,400 --> 00:20:18,600
[DRAMATIC]

358
00:20:22,200 --> 00:20:24,700
[SOBBING]

359
00:20:28,233 --> 00:20:32,833
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

360
00:20:41,667 --> 00:20:46,033
[DRAMATIC]

361
00:20:56,767 --> 00:20:59,233
Ms. Yolly, did you see...

362
00:21:02,600 --> 00:21:03,933
You're here.

363
00:21:06,067 --> 00:21:07,867
Seriously, Marj,

364
00:21:08,133 --> 00:21:09,500
after the chaos and
embarrassment

365
00:21:09,667 --> 00:21:11,600
your mother caused,

366
00:21:11,733 --> 00:21:13,900
you still have the nerve
to show your face?

367
00:21:14,033 --> 00:21:15,500
[HUFFS]

368
00:21:15,633 --> 00:21:17,900
Most people would have the
decency

369
00:21:18,033 --> 00:21:19,733
to disappear out of shame.

370
00:21:22,433 --> 00:21:25,300
Wait, I'm still talking to you!

371
00:21:25,433 --> 00:21:27,267
Can you please,
stay out of this?

372
00:21:27,533 --> 00:21:30,467
Otherwise, I'll take all my
anger out on you!

373
00:21:30,600 --> 00:21:31,767
You know,

374
00:21:32,033 --> 00:21:33,800
this is all your fault.

375
00:21:33,933 --> 00:21:36,433
You were the one who brought
your mother into this mansion.

376
00:21:36,700 --> 00:21:40,900
You destroyed forty years
of marriage between Dad and Mom.

377
00:21:41,033 --> 00:21:42,133
[SCOFFS]

378
00:21:42,300 --> 00:21:44,367
Unbelievable.

379
00:21:44,500 --> 00:21:48,000
Your mother is so embarrassing.

380
00:21:48,267 --> 00:21:50,767
She's already so old,

381
00:21:50,900 --> 00:21:53,300
and she's still flirting?

382
00:21:53,433 --> 00:21:55,833
And she even destroyed
a family.

383
00:21:55,967 --> 00:21:57,967
And it had to be here?

384
00:21:58,100 --> 00:22:00,767
How stupid can she be.

385
00:22:00,900 --> 00:22:04,767
Stop it! If you don't stop
insulting my mother,

386
00:22:04,900 --> 00:22:06,433
I'll smash your mouth!

387
00:22:06,567 --> 00:22:07,700
What?

388
00:22:07,833 --> 00:22:09,867
- [SLAPS]
- [GRUNTS]

389
00:22:10,000 --> 00:22:11,800
You still dare act tough?

390
00:22:13,500 --> 00:22:15,167
And you're playing the victim?

391
00:22:16,433 --> 00:22:18,267
Wake up, Marj!

392
00:22:18,400 --> 00:22:22,400
You are the parasites destroying
this household.

393
00:22:22,533 --> 00:22:26,267
You're a curse
to the Torrecampo family.

394
00:22:26,400 --> 00:22:29,233
Isn't that clear to you yet?

395
00:22:29,367 --> 00:22:33,533
Then this is what you deserve
to wake you up!

396
00:22:33,667 --> 00:22:34,633
[EXCLAIMS]

397
00:22:34,767 --> 00:22:36,667
Stop it, Thea!

398
00:22:37,867 --> 00:22:39,233
- Excuse me.
- [GRUMBLES]

399
00:22:39,367 --> 00:22:41,267
Didn't you see what she did
to me?

400
00:22:41,400 --> 00:22:42,400
I don't care.

401
00:22:42,533 --> 00:22:45,267
I won't allow this fight
to escalate in this house.

402
00:22:45,400 --> 00:22:47,733
Your mother was already
wronged, Edward!

403
00:22:47,867 --> 00:22:50,033
And you're still siding
with Marj?

404
00:22:50,200 --> 00:22:52,000
What did Marj do wrong?

405
00:22:52,133 --> 00:22:53,300
Did Marj get involved with Dad?

406
00:22:53,433 --> 00:22:55,800
Was Marj the one who brought
her mother into the mansion?

407
00:22:55,933 --> 00:22:58,067
Dad was the one who brought
Aunt Evelyn here!

408
00:22:59,433 --> 00:23:01,967
Don't blame Marj
for their mistakes.

409
00:23:04,367 --> 00:23:06,033
Another reason

410
00:23:06,167 --> 00:23:10,400
why I'm not surprised your dad
doesn't like you.

411
00:23:10,533 --> 00:23:14,033
You have no loyalty
to your family.

412
00:23:14,167 --> 00:23:15,800
You don't deserve

413
00:23:15,933 --> 00:23:17,900
to be a Torrecampo.

414
00:23:21,400 --> 00:23:22,800
You belong together!

415
00:23:22,933 --> 00:23:32,900
[INTENSE]

416
00:23:43,833 --> 00:23:45,133
Regina.

417
00:23:45,267 --> 00:23:46,700
What are you doing here?

418
00:23:46,833 --> 00:23:47,933
Get out!

419
00:23:50,767 --> 00:23:53,100
I said get out!

420
00:23:53,233 --> 00:23:55,033
Are you sure?

421
00:23:55,200 --> 00:23:57,600
Go back to our room.

422
00:23:57,733 --> 00:23:59,367
I already changed the bedsheets.

423
00:23:59,500 --> 00:24:00,700
It's clean now.

424
00:24:05,400 --> 00:24:06,767
Clean?

425
00:24:10,400 --> 00:24:12,400
- [SLAPS]
- And you?

426
00:24:16,133 --> 00:24:17,267
Come on!

427
00:24:18,367 --> 00:24:20,800
Is this still a big deal to you?

428
00:24:20,933 --> 00:24:23,367
Haven't you gotten used
to me by now?

429
00:24:23,500 --> 00:24:25,900
Nothing has changed.

430
00:24:26,033 --> 00:24:27,700
I still come home to you.

431
00:24:28,900 --> 00:24:31,800
But you brought your mess
into this house.

432
00:24:31,933 --> 00:24:33,400
You disgust me.

433
00:24:33,533 --> 00:24:35,100
And you expect me to sleep
beside you?

434
00:24:35,233 --> 00:24:37,267
I should have left you
a long time ago!

435
00:24:39,667 --> 00:24:42,500
You've said that so many times.

436
00:24:42,633 --> 00:24:44,167
And yet,

437
00:24:44,300 --> 00:24:45,567
you're still here.

438
00:24:48,667 --> 00:24:53,767
Greg, do you really think I'll
let you live like a bachelor?

439
00:24:53,900 --> 00:24:57,467
I won't make things easy
for you at all.

440
00:24:59,400 --> 00:25:01,000
Please, Regina.

441
00:25:03,033 --> 00:25:05,500
You just don't want to lose
everything

442
00:25:05,633 --> 00:25:07,600
when you leave me.

443
00:25:11,367 --> 00:25:13,667
Oh, Greg.

444
00:25:17,100 --> 00:25:21,500
You think I didn't secure
my finances for myself?

445
00:25:21,633 --> 00:25:22,600
[HUFFS]

446
00:25:22,733 --> 00:25:24,400
I have been doing that
ever since

447
00:25:24,533 --> 00:25:28,033
the first day I found out you
were cheating on me.

448
00:25:28,167 --> 00:25:29,833
So actually,

449
00:25:29,967 --> 00:25:32,933
I will be fine without you.

450
00:25:34,533 --> 00:25:37,700
But because of the betrayal you
did to me,

451
00:25:37,867 --> 00:25:39,533
I will take more.

452
00:25:39,667 --> 00:25:42,400
And you will give me everything

453
00:25:42,533 --> 00:25:43,633
I ask for.

454
00:25:43,767 --> 00:25:45,967
[INTENSE]

455
00:25:54,667 --> 00:25:58,500
Yolly, how long have you been
working for us?

456
00:25:58,633 --> 00:26:03,267
You know what I hate most above
all is being challenged.

457
00:26:05,867 --> 00:26:07,367
That's ridiculous.

458
00:26:07,500 --> 00:26:09,400
If you're really determined
to leave me,

459
00:26:09,567 --> 00:26:12,433
at least grant me
my final request.

460
00:26:12,567 --> 00:26:14,033
Let's do it.

461
00:26:15,067 --> 00:26:17,933
Kind brother!

462
00:26:18,067 --> 00:26:21,200
- [INTENSE]
- [JOBERT EXCLAIMING]

463
00:26:25,933 --> 00:26:28,033
What? Did you see
the cell phone?

464
00:26:28,167 --> 00:26:30,000
It's not in Jobert's things.

465
00:26:30,133 --> 00:26:31,900
Maybe Marj already found it.

466
00:26:32,033 --> 00:26:33,333
I almost forgot.

467
00:26:33,467 --> 00:26:34,400
It's from Ashley.

468
00:26:34,533 --> 00:26:36,267
You might want to have it.

469
00:26:36,400 --> 00:26:38,067
Pack up all your things.

470
00:26:38,200 --> 00:26:39,300
Make sure

471
00:26:39,433 --> 00:26:41,567
it doesn't blow up,
because if it does,

472
00:26:41,700 --> 00:26:44,333
it will destroy our family.

473
00:26:44,500 --> 00:26:46,733
Oh my goodness!

474
00:26:46,867 --> 00:26:48,367
You shameless people!

475
00:26:48,500 --> 00:26:50,967
How could they do this to me?
